# Built retrieval artifacts (rebuilt by POST /index). Also covers
# .kb/faiss_index/ (Stack B's regenerable binary index, per issue #104).
.kb/

# Phase 8 retrieval comparison (eval/paraphrase_comparison/) intermediate state.
# The committed deliverables — queries.yaml, corpus/, wiki/, report.md, and the
# FINAL charts/*.png — are tracked (force-added). These two are NOT: the
# per-paraphrase verdict dumps (churn during metric tuning) and the atomic-write
# temp files. Charts are force-committed once finalised; routine regeneration
# during iteration is otherwise ignored to avoid binary churn (PRD #100 commit
# policy, issue #104).
eval/paraphrase_comparison/results/*.json
eval/paraphrase_comparison/charts/*.tmp

# /raw/ — local-only import inbox (gitignored; use examples/raw/ for samples)
# Leading / anchors the pattern to the repo root so examples/raw/ is NOT ignored.
# Copy examples/raw/*.html into raw/ to try POST /import without committing.
/raw/

# wiki/ — generated artifacts and per-user runtime traces (see wiki/README.md)
wiki/index.md
wiki/lint-report.md
wiki/log.md
wiki/hot.md

# vector_rag/ (Stack B) runtime trace — decoupled from markdown_kb's wiki/log.md
# (issue #103); same append-only Wiki Log discipline, own file.
vector_rag/log.md

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/

# Secrets
.env
.env.local

